gw.api.bean.compare.ui

Class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.bean.compare.ui.EntityDiffDisplay<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    KeyableBeanDiffDisplay

    public class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>
extends Object
implements DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<T>
    Superclass for displaying entity diffs in the policy refresh comparison UI. This class can be used as is or subclassed by customers to give control over the UI or to add errors and warnings. If customers do not specify any particular {@link gw.api.bean.compare.EntityDiff} type for an entity type then this is the type that will be used by default.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      List<DiffDisplay> AllChildren
      Returns all children.
      EntityDiff<KeyableBean> Diff
      The underlying {@link gw.api.bean.compare.EntityDiff} that was passed in when this EntityDiffDisplay was constructed.
      String Label
      Label for rows displaying entities in the policy comparison UI. The default implementation returns a string of the form entityTypeName:entityName (for example Policy:123-456). The entity type name is the display name of the entity type of the EntityDiff, which can be localized by adding a display key of the form entity.TypeName (for example entity.Policy). The entity name is constructed by calling {@link #getEntityName(com.guidewire.commons.entity.KeyableBean)} on either the old value of the entity or, if that is null (as in an add), on the new value of the entity. Subclasses can choose to either override this implementation entirely or to override {@link #getEntityName(com.guidewire.commons.entity.KeyableBean)} to affect just the entityName part of the label.
      String NewValue
      The value to show in the new value column in the policy comparison UI. Default implementation returns the empty string
      String OldValue
      The value to show in the old value column in the policy comparison UI. Default implementation returns the empty string
      DiffDisplay.Type Type
      The default implementation refers to the underlying {@link gw.api.bean.compare.EntityDiff} object to see whether this entity is added, removed, changed or unchanged. Subclasses will rarely need to override this method.
      List<DiffDisplay> VisibleChildren
      Returns all visible children.
